  "response": "There's no universally \"best\" age to get married, as it depends on individual circumstances. However, research and sociological studies suggest some general insights:\n\n1. Late 20s to early 30s is often considered an optimal time for men to marry because:\n- More emotional maturity\n- Better financial stability\n- Clearer understanding of personal goals\n- More developed communication skills\n\n2. Statistically, men who marry between 28-32 tend to have:\n- Lower divorce rates\n- More stable relationships\n- Better economic foundation\n- More emotional preparedness\n\n3. Important considerations beyond age:\n- Personal readiness\n- Emotional maturity\n- Financial stability\n- Compatibility with partner\n- Shared life goals\n\n4. Factors that influence marriage success:\n- Emotional intelligence\n- Communication skills\n- Mutual respect\n- Shared values\n- Commitment\n\n5. Potential risks of marrying too early:\n- Less personal development\n- Financial instability\n- Potential personality changes\n- Less relationship experience\n\nUltimately, the \"best\" age varies for each individual and depends on personal circumstances, emotional readiness, and finding the right partner.",
